  "body": "<!-- This form is for bug reports and feature requests ONLY! \r\n\r\nIf you're looking for help check [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/kubernetes) and the [troubleshooting guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/troubleshooting/).\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n> Uncomment only one, leave it on its own line: \r\n>\r\n> /kind bug\r\n> /kind feature\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nThere will be error when kubelet restarts on a agent if pod in that agent has an azure disk mounted, the error would be like following:\r\nazureDisk - No\r\nt a mounting point for disk andykubewin175-dynamic-pvc-7a0cdeb9-92c7-11e7-b86b-000d3a36d70c on \\var\\lib\\kubelet\\pods\\d146c023-92c7-11e7-b86b-000d3a36d70c\\volumes\\kubernetes.io~azure-disk\\pvc-7a0cdeb9-92c7-11\r\ne7-b86b-000d3a36d70c\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\npod could still works well even if kubelet restarts on the agent\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nconsider following scenario:\r\nA pod mounting an azure disk in a k8s agent\r\nThe kubelet is restarted in that k8s agent\r\nThe pod could not start up, it always reports error as following:\r\n4d 1m 3065 kubelet, 14777acs9000 Warning FailedMount MountVolume.SetUp failed for volume \"pvc-7a0cdeb9-92c7-11e7-b86b-000d3a36d70c\" : azureDisk - No\r\nt a mounting point for disk andykubewin175-dynamic-pvc-7a0cdeb9-92c7-11e7-b86b-000d3a36d70c on \\var\\lib\\kubelet\\pods\\d146c023-92c7-11e7-b86b-000d3a36d70c\\volumes\\kubernetes.io~azure-disk\\pvc-7a0cdeb9-92c7-11\r\ne7-b86b-000d3a36d70c\r\n4d 1m 3157 kubelet, 14777acs9000 Warning FailedMount Error syncing pod\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.7, 1.8\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration**: azure\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n",
